00:33:03.380 --> 00:33:04.640
RETO MEIER: Or I may have
missed the flight.

00:33:04.640 --> 00:33:06.060
IAN NI-LEWIS: Indeed.

00:33:06.060 --> 00:33:08.340
Same thing with the hotel, same
thing with everything.

00:33:08.340 --> 00:33:12.150
The idea is, once you've got
there, you don't need to see

00:33:12.150 --> 00:33:12.710
it anymore.

00:33:12.710 --> 00:33:17.640
So it doesn't need to be updated
perhaps as frequently

00:33:17.640 --> 00:33:19.690
as Foursquare does.

00:33:19.690 --> 00:33:25.460
But it does need to update at
least in time to be able to

00:33:25.460 --> 00:33:28.130
show and hide this
information.

00:33:28.130 --> 00:33:29.570
RETO MEIER: And one of the other
things which I think is

00:33:29.570 --> 00:33:32.890
really important is it needs
to be able to update--

00:33:32.890 --> 00:33:34.120
there's sort of this balance.

00:33:34.120 --> 00:33:36.540
Because if something does
change, if my flight time

00:33:36.540 --> 00:33:39.500
changes or my hotel booking
changes, I need to see that

00:33:39.500 --> 00:33:40.830
updated straightaway.

00:33:40.830 --> 00:33:42.770
And that needs to be as low
latency as possible.

00:33:42.770 --> 00:33:46.030
But the frequency of that
is pretty rare.

00:33:46.030 --> 00:33:48.990
Once the travel is booked,
you're going to be lucky if

00:33:48.990 --> 00:33:51.066
there's a change once
a day, if that.

00:33:51.066 --> 00:33:51.550
IAN NI-LEWIS: Indeed.

00:33:51.550 --> 00:33:54.030
You certainly don't want to be
checking every five minutes to

00:33:54.030 --> 00:33:55.130
see if your flight's delayed.

00:33:55.130 --> 00:33:58.050
Instead, what you really want
is to know exactly when your

00:33:58.050 --> 00:33:59.710
flight's delayed and
then never worry

00:33:59.710 --> 00:34:01.440
about it again, right?

00:34:01.440 --> 00:34:04.630
So if I was doing this with just
my airline, my airline is

00:34:04.630 --> 00:34:07.340
going to send me an SMS
to let me know that

00:34:07.340 --> 00:34:08.190
the flight's delayed.

00:34:08.190 --> 00:34:10.570
Now I don't want TripIt to send
me an SMS because there's

00:34:10.570 --> 00:34:12.550
a better way to do
that, right?

00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:14.270
RETO MEIER: Absolutely.

00:34:14.270 --> 00:34:15.480
You would want to--

00:34:15.480 --> 00:34:17.310
yeah, exactly.

00:34:17.310 --> 00:34:19.900
IAN NI-LEWIS: In fact, I think
what we want is to--

00:34:19.900 --> 00:34:22.080
hopefully what it
